              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCY"
                ],
                "institute": "2UK HAR"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Harwell synchrocyclotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-BE"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Protons from synchrocyclotron with",
                " a maximum energy of 170 MeV impinging onto",
                " a Be-target of 0.25 inch thickness. The n-beam",
                " was confined to a diameter of 2 inches by",
                " means of a concrete shielding."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron spectrum ranged from about 50 to 170 MeV,",
                " with a peak near 140 MeV. A graph of the spectrum",
                " is given in figure 8 of the main reference.",
                " The quantity 'En-mean' is a spectrum averaged",
                " energy between the limits 'En-min' and 'En-max'.",
                " it is called the 'effective energy' in the main",
                " reference. The quantity 'En-err' is the error in",
                " 'En-mean' and arises from the error in the",
                " measured spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Both samples (polyethylene and carbon) were",
                " 5 inches long an 1.5 inches wide. They were",
                " 100-200 microns thick.",
                " The polyethylene sample was cut from a sheet",
                " of about 100 microns thickness. It consisted",
                " of 100% pure (C-H(2))(n). The thickness",
                " was 10.54 +-0.01 mg/cm**2.",
                " The carbon sample was prepared by drying out",
                " of aquadag which had been diluted in water,",
                " in a metal mould. Removal of the dry C-film",
                " was facilitated by the use of a wet sheet of",
                " cellophane tightly stretched over the base of",
                " the mould. Its thickness was 13.62 +- 0.03 mg/cm**2",
                " and was chosen so as to produce the same energy",
                " loss as the polyethylene target film. It consisted",
                " of 93.4% carbon, 1% hydrogen and 5.6% oxygen."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measurement of the angular distributions of the",
                " recoiling particles from a carbon scatterer and from",
                " a polyethylene scatterer.",
                " The difference yields the amounts of protons recoiling",
                "from hydrogen nuclei as a function of the recoil angles",
                " From these amounts the hydrogen elastic scattering",
                " angular distributions can be derived.",
                " The proton angles are determined by the analysis",
                " of the proton tracks in a photographic emulsion.",
                " The proton energies are determined from",
                " the ranges of the protons in this emulsion.",
                " From this proton energy the neutron energy",
                " can be derived."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Scattering chamber under a pressure of",
                " 1.E-2 cm Hg containing four 1.5 um thick glass plates",
                " coated with a 600 micron layer of Ilford C2",
                " photographic emulsion and a 25 micron supercoat of",
                " Ilford G5 emulsion.",
                " The four plates were held at angles of 54, 44, 34",
                " and 24 degrees to the neutron beam.",
                " The plates at 44,34 and 24 degerees were behind",
                " aluminium absorbers designed to bring most of",
                " recoils to rest in the emulsion. Unfortunately",
                " the effect of multiple scattering in the",
                " aluminium was too large, and it was not possible",
                " to use the measurements on the plates at 34 and",
                " 24 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Background from scattering by the nylon",
                " thread used to suspend the samples.",
                " Interactions of the neutrons with the C-nuclei."
              ]
            }
          ],
